casebody.data:
Shahean JONES, Appellant,
v.
STATE of Missouri, Respondent. No. ED 106175 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, DIVISION ONE. Filed: October 16, 2018
Application for Transfer to Supreme Court Denied November 19, 2018
Application for Transfer to Supreme Court Denied January 29, 2019 FOR APPELLANT: Michael A. Gross, 231 South Bemiston Ave., Ste. 250, St. Louis, MO 63105. FOR RESPONDENT: Joshua D. Hawley, Attorney General, Shaun J. Mackelprang, Asst. Atty. Gen., P.O. Box 899, Jefferson City, MO 65102. Before Roy L. Richter, P.J., Robert M. Clayton III, J., and Angela T. Quigless, J.

ORDER

PER CURIAM.

Shahean Jones appeals the judgment dismissing his "Motion to Reopen Proceeding for Post-Conviction Relief." We find no error has occurred.

No jurisprudential purpose would be served by a written opinion. We have, however, provided the parties a memorandum setting forth the reasons for our decision. The judgment of the motion court is affirmed under Rule 84.16(b).
